<H1>Short Assignment #1</H1>
<HR>

<H3>The purpose of this assignment is to use keyboard input, formatted =
output to=20
the monitor, variables, arithmetic formulas, selection structures, and =
symbolic=20
constants.</H3>
<HR>

<H3>Program Requirements:</H3>
<P>Write a program which determines the cost of a speeding ticket. =
Calculate the=20
total cost of the ticket based on the speed of the violator and the =
speed limit.=20
Print the total cost of the ticket on the monitor.</P>
<OL>
  <LI>
  <P>Prompt the user for the speed limit and the speed of the =
driver.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Calculate the ticket cost as $50 plus:</P>
  <OL>
    <LI type=3Da>
    <P>0% additional if the driver's speed was 10 or less miles per hour =
above=20
    the speed limit.</P>
    <LI type=3Da>
    <P>5% additional if driver's speed was more than 10 miles per hour =
above the=20
    speed limit.</P>
    <LI type=3Da>
    <P>10% additional if driver's speed was more than 15 miles per hour =
above=20
    the speed limit</P>
    <LI type=3Da>
    <P>15% additional if driver's speed was more than 20 miles per hour =
above=20
    the speed limit.</P>
    <LI type=3Da>
    <P>20% additional if driver's speed was more than 25 miles per hour =
above=20
    the speed limit.</P>
    <LI type=3Da>
    <P>25% additional if driver's speed was 30 or more miles per hour =
above the=20
    speed limit.</P>
    <LI type=3Da>
    <P>Do not charge a fine if the driver wasn't =
speeding.</P></LI></OL></LI></OL>
<OL start=3D2>
  <LI>
  <P>Display to the user the values which were input (speed limit and =
driver's=20
  speed) and the calculated ticket fine amount. Print 2 decimals for the =
fine=20
  amount. Make sure your output format matches the <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www2.seminolestate.edu/dgrant/career_pathways/short_assign=
ments/ShortAssignment1/sample_output_for_short_assign1.htm"=20
  target=3D_blank>sample output.</A></P>
  <LI>
  <P>You can run your program multiple times to test multiple speed =
limits and=20
  driver speeds. Looping is not required for this assignment. Just run =
your=20
  program again with a different set of input numbers.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Use a symbolic constant for the base ticker fine rate ($50).</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Name your source file SpeedTrap.cpp.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>This short assignment does not require comments. You should still =
follow=20
  the coding standards introduced to this =
point.</P></LI></OL></BODY></HTML>

